<SLUG> BC-Haiti-Priest Slain,0164 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Roman Catholic priest killed by Haiti gunmen
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PORT-AU-PRINCE, Haiti (AP) _ Gunmen shot and killed a Roman
Catholic priest active in organizing Haiti's peasants, state TV
said.
	   The Rev. Jean Pierre-Louis was accosted by two gunmen as he got
out of his car in his office courtyard around late Monday morning,
a street vendor who said he witnessed the slaying told the station.
	   Haitian Human Rights Platform director Chenet Jean-Baptiste said
he believed it was a political killing, and noted Pierre-Louis was
not robbed. The identity of the gunmen was not known.
	   Once a follower of former President Jean-Bertrand Aristide,
Pierre-Louis distanced himself from Aristide heirs who have
governed Haiti since 1996.
	   Persecuted by anti-democratic soldiers and thugs during past
dictatorships, Pierre-Louis had often been forced to go into
hiding. He was recently active in organizing peasant associations,
among other causes.
</TEXT>
