<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Costa Rica-Homosexuals,0151 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Critics drive Costa Rican homosexual festival into secrecy
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SAN JOSE, Costa Rica (AP) _ Organizers of a homosexual festival
have taken the once-overt event into secrecy after criticism by
President Miguel Angel Rodriguez and a Roman Catholic archbishop.
	   Organizers of the Costa Rican Lesbi-Gay Festival 98 announced
Monday they would change the site of the Aug. 26-31 event and halt
publicity.
	   ``We don't want the country to be known for activities of this
sort, but for peace, protection of nature and respect for human
rights,'' Rodriguez had told reporters.
	   The archbishop of San Jose, Roman Arrieta, said he was in
``total disagreement'' with the festival, which he said was
``contrary to the healthy customs of the Costa Rican people.''
	   The festival had been planned for the beach of Quepos, 35 miles
(56 kilometers) south of the capital.
</TEXT>
