<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Market Stalls </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Unemployed turn out in droves for chance at Bangkok market stalls
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ More than 8,000 poor and unemployed
Thais turned up at Bangkok's city hall to apply for about 600
stalls available at two city-run markets, local papers reported
Tuesday.
	   An advisor to the Bangkok governor said the demand was
overwhelming and that the city would try and open more markets to
accommodate people who wanted stalls, The Nation newspaper said.
	   Thailand's economy is in deep recession and more than two
million people have been left unemployed by the country's economic
crisis, which began in July 1997. 	   
</TEXT>
