r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  Computerproblemshutsdown     08-04 0118
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> Computer problem shuts down Japanese bank's ATM network </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ A major Japanese bank's nationwide automatic teller
machine network has been crippled by a computer system malfunction,
an Asahi Bank Ltd. spokesman said Tuesday.
	   The computer error, the cause of which remains unknown,
paralyzed Asahi Bank's ATM network shortly after 10:00 a.m. local
time (0100 GMT), said bank spokesman Masahiro Minami.
	   The spokesman said the bank sped efforts to fix the problem, but
he was unable to say when its hundreds of ATMs would be back in
service.
	   One of Japan's 10 largest commercial banks, Asahi Bank was
formed through the merger of Kyowa Bank and Saitama Bank in 1991.
 &UR; (cd) 	   
</TEXT>
