<HEADLINE>
Lightning kills parents, daughter in Iran
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TEHRAN, Iran (AP) _ Three members of an Iranian farm family were
killed when they were struck by lightning, the official Islamic
Republic News Agency reported Tuesday.
	   It said an 18-year-old girl, her 65-year-old father and
55-year-old mother were working on their farm in the central Arak
province on Monday when the lightning struck. The report gave no
other details.
	   More than 30 people died Saturday in northern Iran in flash
floods caused by heavy rains.
