<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-Crow Shooting </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Crow shooting contest organized to clean city skyline
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ Determined to reduce the nuisance
caused by crows, city officials in a Kuala Lumpur suburb are
offering prizes to those who shoot the birds down.
	   A crow shooting contest set for Aug. 16 in Klang is offering one
ringgit (dlrs 0.25) for every crow shot, the Star newspaper
reported Tuesday.
	   Rosli Udin, Klang Municipal Council spokesman, said the crows
were a nuisance to the public and their population had to be
reduced.
	   Rosli said the event, organized by the town's health department,
was open to both professional and amateur shooters.
	   In the past, the council set traps in public parks to capture
crows. Last year, 35,620 crows were killed by the traps, a
municipal official said.	   
</TEXT>
