<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Germany-House Explosion </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Presumed gas explosion destroys apartment house in Berlin
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BERLIN (AP) _ A suspected natural gas explosion destroyed an
apartment house in Berlin early Tuesday and rescue workers searched
by hand and with dogs through the rubble for survivors.
	   Firefighters said at least nine of the 19 people registered as
living in the five-story building survived; at least two of them
were injured.
	   Some 200 rescue workers and five dogs were searching for trapped
residents. Heavy equipment could not be used for fear the 5-meter
(16-foot) high pile of rubble would collapse further.
	   Police believe the explosion, which sent a huge cloud of dust
over the Steglitz neighborhood, was caused by natural gas.
Residents of six surrounding homes were evacuated as a precaution.
 &UR; (pfg-gb)
