</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ President Boris Yeltsin resumed his summer
vacation Tuesday, arriving at the Valdai lake resort in
northwestern Russia, presidential press service announced.
	   Last week, Yeltsin interrupted his stay in the Russian republic
of Karelia, near the Finnish border, citing urgent business in
Moscow.
	   He spent the past few days in his country residence near the
Russian capital, conferring with Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko
and other top officials and signing several economic bills into
law.
	   Yeltsin is expected to spend about 10 days in the Uzhin resort
near lake Valdai, about 400 kilometers (230 miles) north of Moscow,
Interfax news agency reported, citing Yeltsin's press service.
