<HEADLINE>
Presumed gas explosion destroys apartment house in Berlin
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with 2 trapped in rubble, eight missing; CORRECTS to 4
story &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BERLIN (AP) _ A suspected natural gas explosion destroyed an
apartment house in Berlin early Tuesday, trapping at least two
people in a huge pile of rubble.
	   Firefighters had made contact with two trapped survivors and
were working to extricate them, but the fate of eight other people
registered as living in the four-story building was unknown.
	   One couple that managed to get out told rescuers their
13-year-old son was still trapped inside.
	   There was no immediate word on injuries.
	   Some 200 rescue workers searched by hand and with dogs through
the rubble. Heavy equipment could not be used for fear the 5-meter
(16-foot) high pile of rubble would collapse further.
	   Police believe the explosion, which sent a huge cloud of dust
over the Steglitz neighborhood, was caused by natural gas.
Residents of six surrounding homes were evacuated as a precaution.
