<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Floods </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Floods in eastern Russia leave 6,000 homeless
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Two swollen rivers in the southeastern region of
Chita have flooded 32 settlements and left more than 6,000 people
homeless, a news report said Tuesday.
	   Emergency workers, including police and army troops, were
evacuating residents from settlements along the Shilka and Nercha
rivers, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   Local officials declared a state of emergency in the region. No
deaths have been linked to the flooding.
	   Weather forecasters said high water levels may persist until the
weekend, when a hurricane that swept in from Mongolia was likely to
dissipate, according to ITAR-Tass.
	   (nw/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
