<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Philippines-Shooting </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Philippine police chief accused of killing prisoner in target
</HEADLINE>
practice &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MANILA, Philippines (AP) _ The National Police Commission said
Tuesday it is investigating a police chief accused of fatally
shooting a prisoner while trying to hit a plastic bottle placed on
the inmate's shoulder.
	   Prisoner San-ur Sibay was killed July 22 in Kabugao in northern
Kalinga Apayao province, said police commission Vice Chairman Leo
Magahum.
	   Magahum said police chief Marner Dasayon reported that he shot
Sibay after the prisoner grabbed a gun from a police escort in an
escape attempt.
	   But witnesses said Dasayon forced Sibay to stand still and
placed a plastic bottle on his shoulder for target practice.
Dasayon's shot missed the bottle and hit Sibay in the neck, killing
him, they said.
	   Ambaro Sagle, Sibay's uncle, said Dasayon was drunk at the time
of the shooting.
	   ``He was bragging about how good a gun expert he was,'' Sagle
said. ``He made my nephew into a toy for target practice.''
	   Sibay reportedly was to have been released in a few days after
charges of causing serious injuries in a fight were dropped.
	   Congressman Elias Bulut filed a case against Dasayon with the
police commission, which investigates police wrongdoing, after no
report of the incident was filed in Kabugao.
	   ``I wish to state that we are still government by the rule of
law and not of man,'' Bulut said. ``The act of summarily executing
a mere suspect of a crime in public view is the highest degree of
barbarism.''
	   No formal charges have been filed against Dasayon, and he has
not been relieved of his duty.	   
</TEXT>
