</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Counterfeiters </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian police detain scores of suspected counterfeiters
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ Ukrainian authorities have detained more
than 400 suspected counterfeiters and uncovered more than 2,300
cases of fake currency notes being distributed in the first half of
this year, a newspaper reported Tuesday.
	   Police also found 16 workshops producing counterfeit Ukrainian
hryvna, U.S. dollars, Russian rubles and Italian lira, Kievskiye
Vedomosti said, citing the Interior Ministry.
	   A total of 440 people involved in producing and distributing
counterfeit money were facing charges, the report added.
	   Most of the fake money was produced with the help of computers
and color printers or photo copiers, it said. Counterfeiters favor
10- and 20-hryvna notes, worth dlrs 5 to 10 at the current exchange
rate, which they then try to dispose of in outlying villages,
according to the report.
	   (sms/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
