<SLUG> BC-Czech-Havel </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Havel develops pneumonia, irregular heartbeat
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ President Vaclav Havel suffered
from an irregular heartbeat on Tuesday and has developed pneumonia,
doctors said.
	   A statement from the presidential spokesman did not classify
Havel's immediate condition but said the situation ``is being
worked on intensively.''
	   ``The course of the president's treatment was complicated by
arrhythmia this morning,'' spokesman Martin Krafl said.
	   According to the statement, the beginning of pneumonia was
confirmed by computer tomography.
	   Havel remains in intensive care after undergoing surgery on July
26 to close a colostomy.
	   (oh/dc)
