<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Albania-Kosovo </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Kosovo boy killed by robbers in Albania
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TIRANA, Albania (AP) _ An 8-year-old boy from Kosovo was killed
and four other refugees from the embattled Serbian province were
wounded when robbers attacked them in Albania, newspapers reported
Tuesday.
	   The attack reportedly occurred early Monday near Lezha, 55
kilometers (35 miles) north of the capital Tirana. The assailants,
wearing masks, shot at the minibus carrying nine refugees when the
driver refused their demands to stop, the independent papers Gazeta
Shqiptare and Koha Jone said.
	   Six people were arrested in the attack, according to the
newspapers. Police did not immediately confirm the report.
	   More than 12,000 refugees from Kosovo have fled their homes into
Albania in the past several months to escape violent clashes that
began following a crackdown by Serb-led security forces on Kosovo
Albanian separatists. Hundreds of others have died.
	   (ac/dc)
</TEXT>
