<HEADLINE>
Dollar down, gold up
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar fell against other major
currencies in early European trading Tuesday. Gold rose.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Monday:
	   _1.7812 German marks, down from 1.7840
	   _144.81 Japanese yen, down from 145.81
	   _1.5000 Swiss francs, down from 1.5010
	   _5.9694 French francs, down from 5.9818
	   _2.0087 Dutch guilders, own from 2.0116
	   _1,757.54 Italian lire, down from 1,759.90
	   _1.5136 Canadian dollars, down from 1.5160
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6296, up from dlrs
1.6288.
	   London dealers fixed a recommended gold price of dlrs 285.70 bid
per troy ounce at midmorning, up from dlrs 284.10 Monday.
	   In Zurich gold traded at dlrs 285.70, up from dlrs 283.60.
	   Gold dropped 30 cents in Hong Kong to dlrs 286.25.
	   Silver opened in London at dlrs 5.35 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 5.40.
	   (rb)
</TEXT>
