<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Hungary-Heat Wave </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Record-breaking heat wave has Budapest panting
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) _ Hungarians are sweltering in a heat
wave that has buckled streetcar tracks and sent temperatures
soaring to record highs this week.
	   Public pools have standing room only, residents are plunging
into city fountains to seek relief and doctors are warning the
elderly in this city of nearly 2 million people to stay home.
	   A 77-year-old heat record for Aug. 3 was broken Monday when the
official temperature reached 36.7 degrees Celsius (98 Fahrenheit).
It was even hotter downtown _ 40 (104 F) or higher.
	   The heat wave is in its third week.
	   ``We just can't work _ we have three fans going and it is still
35 (95 F) degrees in the office,'' sairtain stretches where
there's danger of the track getting overheated,'' said State
Railways official Gyoergy Foeldhazi.
	   No deaths have been reported directly due to heat, but the
municipal ambulance service said its workload is up by 20 percent.
	   A break in the weather is coming _ but not for long. Attila
Nadrai, head of the National Meteorological Service, said a cool
front is expected by Wednesday but the forecast for next week is
more heat.
	   (ab/dc)
</TEXT>
