<SLUG> BC-Sports-Cycling-Tour of Italy-Vatican </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
2000 Tour to start at St. Peter's Square
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ Italy's leading cycling race will mark the new
millennium in a special way.
	   Organizers announced Tuesday that the first leg of the Tour of
Italy in 2000 will be dedicated to the city of Rome and the
Vatican's Holy Year.
	   The leg will be raced on May 13, concluding in St. Peter's
Square with the racers and officials to pay homage to the pope,
said La Gazzetta dello Sport, the sports daily that organizes the
cycling classic.
	   (vls) 	   
