<HEADLINE>
Wild bear injures woman, appears in village
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ A wild bear attacked and injured a woman in
the forest in western Ukraine and then appeared in a nearby
village, frightening its residents, a newspaper said Tuesday.
	   The male bear attack occurred when the woman was picking
raspberries in a forest in the Ivano-Frankivsk region, the daily
Segodnya said. The animal later turned up in the village of Spas.
	   Local hunters chased the male bear out of their settlement and
later found the dead body of a female bear in the forest. The
female bear had apparently been killed by poachers, the report
said.
