<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Auto Exports </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Thai auto exports up 84.7 percent in first half of 1998
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Thailand's vehicle exports in this
year's first half rose 84.7 percent from January-June last year to
18.29 billion baht (dlrs 446 million), the Federation of Thai
Industries' auto club said Tuesday.
	   The club gave no explanation for the increase. Its data show
that car exports recorded the highest growth rate, jumping 144
percent from 1997's first half to 11.35 billion baht (dlrs 276
million).
	   Exports of automobile components ranked second in terms of
growth, soaring 74.3 percent to 1.88 billion baht (dlrs 45
million).
	   With domestic sales slumping because of Thailand's economic
crisis, Thai automakers are focusing their sales strategies toward
exports.
	   Most Thai automakers are joint ventures with the top Japanese
car companies, which dominate the local market.	   
</TEXT>
