<SLUG> BC-EU-France </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EU approves dlrs 39 million to support French defense conversion
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) - The European Union approved 35.5
million European currency units Tuesday (dlrs 39 million) to
support French regions facing severe job losses due to reconversion
of the defense industry.
	   The EU Commission said the funds will be used in 22 areas in
France where employment is particularly threatened by restructuring
of the defense sector.
	   The defense sector in France accounts for 670,000 jobs. The
restructuring of defence activities decided in 1997 is likely to
result in the loss of about 35,000 jobs over the next few years,
the Commission said.
	   It said the French government is also financing 19 regional
programs linked to industrial conversion and 17 others specifically
tied to conversion of areas affected by the decline in
defense-related activities.
	   Altogether, EU and French funds included, ``the total cost of
the multiregional program is estimated at 136.3 million ecu (dlrs
150 million),'' the EU statement said.
	   Of that sum, ``62.5 million ecu (dlrs 69 million) comes from the
private sector, 35.4 million ecu (dlrs 39 million) from the French
authorities and 38.4 million ecu (dlrs 42 million) from'' the EU,
the statement said.
	   France, along with other European countries with declining
defense budgets in the post-Cold War era, has accelerated its push
to consolidate its defense and aerospace industries.
	    &UR; (as-ju)
</TEXT>
