<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Heat Wave </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Heat wave hits Ukraine
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photo Planned &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ A heat wave has swept over parts of
Ukraine, sending temperatures in southern regions to record highs
of 40 Centigrade (104 Fahrenheit, a meteorological official said
Tuesday.
	   The weather service attributed the heat wave to hot air coming
from southwestern Europe.
	   ``Such hot periods are rare,'' said Mycola Kulbida, head of the
Ukraine's Meteorological Center. ``They occur once in 20 years.''
	   Ukraine usually has mild summer weather, but the temperature hit
record highs of 40 Centigrade (104 Fahrenheit) in the southern
cities of Mykolayiv and Kherson.
	   In the capital Kiev, the temperature was about 35 Centigrade (95
Fahrenheit).
	   Ukraine suffered storms and floods in the western part of the
country earlier this summer, and Kulbida said there was ``an
extreme danger of fire'' in southern Ukraine because of the high
temperatures.
	   No major change in the weather was forecast until the end of the
week, he said.
	   (ms/sms/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
