<HEADLINE>
Clarke moves into No. 2 spot on European Tour money list
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   VIRGINIA WATER, England (AP) _ Darren Clarke moved into No. 2
spot on the European Tour money list after finishing second in the
Scandinavian Masters at Stockholm on Sunday.
	   The Northern Ireland golfer finished three strokes behind Jesper
Parnevik to claim the dlrs 146,200 second prize at Stockholm and
jump Colin Montgomerie and Ernie Els to move from No. 4 spot to No.
2 on the European Tour.
	   The Scandinavian Masters was Clarke's second successive top ten
finish on the tour. His second place at the Dutch Open on July 26
had boosted him from No.6 place on the tour to No.4.
	   Lee Westwood still leads the tour with dlrs 970,593, ahead of
Clarke with dlrs 777,336, Montgomerie with dlrs 710,683 and South
Africa's Ernie Els dropping into No.4 spot with dlrs 635,832.
	   The remainder of the European Tour top ten remained unchanged.
	   (jp)
