<SLUG> BC-EU-Peru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EU clears dlrs 2.1 million in aid for Peru
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) - The European Union on Tuesday approved
1.95 million European currency units (dlrs 2.1 million) in
humanitarian aid for Peru.
	   The EU Commission said the funds will be used to help resettle
thousands of Peruvian refugees who fled civil conflict in the
country's rural areas in recent years.
	   ``Hundreds of thousands of people fled during the violence that
has affected Peru for over 12 years. Many are now returning, but
are having great difficulty resettling on land that was abandoned
for many years,'' the Commission said.
	   Funds are scarce in Peru, which is still recovering from
torrential rains and floods earlier this year attributed to the El
Nino phenomenon, the statement said.
	   The funds for returning refugees will be channeled through
humanitarian organizations for projects being carried out over the
next eight months.
	    &UR; (as)
