<SLUG> BC-Vatican-France-Immigrants </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Vatican calls for respect for law by occupiers
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   VATICAN CITY (AP) _ The Vatican on Tuesday called on a group of
immigrants occupying its embassy in Paris for four days to end
their ``illegal action.''
	   In a note seeking to clarify its position, the Vatican stressed
the need to obey French laws by immigrants seeking residence
permits.
	   In its first official comment Monday, the Vatican put the number
of people occupying its embassy at 12. But its note Tuesday said
they were actually nine -- four foreigners and five French citizens
from various associations.
	   The Vatican initially said its diplomats had asked French
authorities to review the cases of the immigrants seeking residence
permits. Its latest note acknowledged the ``human drama'' of those
involved, but emphasized that the problems involved ``must be
solved in respect of the law.''
	   (vls)
