<SLUG> BC-Greece-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Portuguese man arrested on heroin trafficking charges
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ALEXANDROUPOLIS, Greece (AP) _ Customs officials on the
Greek-Turkish border arrested a Portuguese man on drug trafficking
charges after he was found to be in possession of 3.3 kilograms
(7.2 pounds) of heroin, authorities said Tuesday.
	   Officials at the Kipos customs post on the Greek-Turkish border
arrested Fernando Costa dos Santos, 28, late on Monday after a
search of his luggage revealed the heroin hidden in the lining of a
leather shoulder bag and a large leather notebook.
	   Dos Santos, a resident of London, arrived at the border crossing
by bus from Istanbul. He told authorities he was to be paid dlrs
5,000 to transport the heroin from Istanbul to London.
	   The man is being held in custody and is due to appear before a
prosecutor.
	   (eb) 	   
</TEXT>
