<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Grolsch Open </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Arazi thrown out of Dutch Open
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: will be updated with later matches &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) _ Moroccan Hicham Arazi was thrown
out of the Grolsch Open tennis tourney Tuesday for unsportsmanlike
conduct at 7-6 (11-9), 1-5 against Swede Magnus Norman.
	   Arazi had already been warned by the umpire twice for throwing
his racket, as he grew increasingly angry with himself for making
errors in the second set of this first-round match.
	   When he several times deliberately hit the ball wildly out of
bounds in an apparent attempt to throw the second set, he was given
a third warning and an automatic disqualification.
	   Arazi, ranked 42 in the world, will forfeit his prize money and
may be fined by the ATP tour administration.
	   Top-seeded Slovakian Karol Kucera met unexpected resistance from
75th-ranked Russian Marat Safin, but struggled through to the last
16 of this clay court tournament, 6-2, 3-6, 7-6 (7-5).
	   (sc)	   
</TEXT>
