<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1334 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   The upper atmosphere remained unstable across the local region
Tuesday due to a nearly stationary low-pressure system located
across the Atlantic east through northeast of the Bahamas.
	   A trough has developed extending from this circulation
southeastward across our local area, aiding in development of
thunderstorms Monday evening and overnight.
	   Similar results are also possible Tuesday afternoon and Tuesday
night across our region, with very heavy rainfall possible.
	   An upper-level disturbance in the easterly winds moved quickly
across the tropical Atlantic and into the Lesser Antilles Monday
night and Tuesday morning. It is expected to reach our southeast
coastal waters late Tuesday afternoon or this evening.
	   However, dry and stable low level air has begun to move ahead of
this disturbance into the Virgin Islands late Tuesday morning and
will arrive in Puerto Rico Tuesday afternoon.
	   The drier air is expected to limit the number of showers and
thunderstorms developing across the area through Tuesday evening
before an increase in low-level moisture and active weather occurs
Tuesday and Wednesday.
	   East-northeast winds around 15 knots were building into the
local coastal waters from the east late Tuesday morning and will
cause a mild increase in seas across the regional waters.
	   Mariners across the east and southeast waters are urged to keep
an alert eye to the sky Tuesday afternoon and evening as clusters
of thunderstorms move in from the east.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms. High near 90. Wind east to northeast 15
mph and gusty.
	   Tonight... Becoming partly cloudy in the west. Variably cloudy
in the east. Scattered showers and isolated coastal thunderstorms,
most numerous in the east. Low 70 to 80. Wind east 5 mph. Chance of
rain 40 percent.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy and becoming breezy. A 50 percent
chance of showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind northeast
15 to 20 mph.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of
showers or thunderstorms. High 70 to 75 in the mountains, 85 to 90
in lower elevations. Wind becoming northeast-east at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with scattered showers and isolated
thunderstorms. Low from around 65 on mountain peaks, 75 to 80 in
lower elevations. Wind northeast 5 to 10 mph. Chance of rain 50
percent.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy with a 50 percent chance of showers
and thunderstorms. Breezy in higher elevations. High from 70 to 75
in the mountains, 85 to 90 low elevations. Wind northeast 10 to 20
mph.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to 95. Wind east around 15 mph
except northeast along the coast.
	   Tonight... Becoming partly cloudy in the west. Variably cloudy
in the east. Scattered showers and isolated thunderstorms, mainly
in the east. Low 70 to 80. Wind light from the northeast. Chance of
rain 40 percent.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy. A 50 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 80 to 90. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Increasing cloudiness leading to a 40 percent
chance of showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to
20 mph, except variable less than 10 mph along the west coast in
the afternoon.
	   Tonight... Becoming partly cloudy. A 20 percent chance of
showers or lingering thunderstorms, mainly in the evening. Low 65
to 75. Wind light and variable.
	   Wednesday... Becoming mostly cloudy and breezy. A 50 percent
chance of showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east 15 to
25 mph, except variable less than 10 mph along the west coast in
the afternoon.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Increasing cloudiness, leading to a 30 percent
chance of showers and thunderstorms. High from 70 to 80 in the
mountains, 80 to 90 in lower elevations. Wind becoming northeast 10
to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Becoming partly cloudy in the west. Variably cloudy
in the east. Scattered showers and isolated thunderstorms, mostly
in the east. Low 65 to 75. Wind northeast 5 to 10 mph. Chance of
rain 40 percent.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy and becoming breezy. A 50 percent
chance of showers and thunderstorms. High from 70 to 80 in the
mountains, 80 to 90 in lower elevations. Wind northeast 15 to 20
mph.
