	   Wednesday night through Saturday... Moderate high pressure to
prevail across the northeast Caribbean. The next tropical wave will
move into the local area Thursday. Wind will be northeast 15 to 20
kt through Thursday, seas 5 to 7 ft. Wind shifting east to
southeast and decreasing after wave passage Friday through
Saturday.
