<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Abou-Malaria </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bradford calls off transfer after French forward falls ill
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRADFORD, England (AP) _ Samassi Abou's transfer from West Ham
to Bradford was called off Tuesday when it was discovered the
French Under-21 international forward was suffering from malaria.
	   Abou was thought to have contracted the disease during an
off-season visit to the Ivory Coast. He delayed his visit to Valley
Parade because of flu-like symptoms.
	   After medical tests in London, malaria was diagnosed and the
player is having treatment in hospital.
	   ``Samassi had been running a temperature of over 100 degrees and
blood tests have shown he has contracted malaria,'' said Bradford
owner Geoffrey Richmond, who was about to pay West Ham 900,000
pounds (dlrs 1.48 million) for the forward.
	   ``The two clubs doctors have spoken and as a result of that
conversation we have decided to put the transfer on hold.''
	   (rjm)	   
