<HEADLINE>
It took three months, but summer comes _ finally _ to Britain
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS conversion for Fahrenheit graf 3
 &UR; By MARA BELLABY &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ When Fabrizio Pellizzetti moved here from his
native Italy four weeks ago, friends warned him he would miss the
sun and balmy skies. How right they were.
	   Even in a country known for its gray, overcast days, this summer
has tested Britons' resilience, as they awoke day after day to
clouds and the hint of rain.
	   But Tuesday, all that seemed to be changing _ or at least people
chose to believe it was _ as forecasts called for the sudden
appearance of sunny days and temperatures in the mid-80s Fahrenheit
(around 30 Celsius) through the weekend in most of the country.
