<SLUG> BC-Sports-Basketball-Worlds, 3rd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Spain, Russia win key games as second round comes to end
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS quote from Lithuanian coach on Karnisovas injury &QL; 
 &UR; By STEPHEN WADE &QC; 
 &UR; AP Sports Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Spain defeated Lithuania 86-80 in overtime
and Russia won over Canada 81-72 to pick up key victories Tuesday
in second-round games of the World Championship, moving their
records to 5-1 entering Friday's crucial quarterfinals.
	   Spain, the surprise team of the worlds, hasn't won a medal in a
major tournament in seven years _ bronze in the '91 Europeans _ and
has hardly been heard from since it shocked itself with silver in
the 1984 Olympics.
	   Forward Alberto Herreros, the leading scorer in the tournament,
had 27 and Alfonso Reyes added 19. Arturas Karnisovas, playing with
a bandaged head after a second-half collision with a Spain's
Ignacio de Miguel that drew blood, led Lithuania (4-2) with 20. But
he was scoreless in the last 11 minutes.
	   ``I think that (injury) hurt him at the end of the game,'' said
Lithuanaia coach Jonas Kazlauskas.
	   Spain, leading most of the way,could have won in regulation but
Herreros missed an outside shot in the final seconds and Carlos
Jimenez missed a tip-in at the gun.
	   ``This has shown our basketball is decent and we're
competitive,'' said coach Lolo Sainz, who is in the first phase of
rebuilding and is expected in the next few years to dip heavily
into a rich pool of young talent.
	   ``We're not afraid of anybody,'' he added.
	   Russia _ billed as the favorite with Yugoslavia to win the title
Sunday _ was topped by Vassiliy Karassev with 21 points and Sergei
Babkov and Sergei Panov with 14. Canada (1-5) got 14 points and 11
rebounds from Greg Newton.
	   Spain and Russia were already guaranteed quarterfinal places.
Four other teams also have spots _ Greece, Yugoslavia, Lithuania
and the United States.
	   The two other places were to be decided later Tuesday with four
teams in the running _ Italy, Argentina, Puerto Rico and Australia.
	   Italy faced Puerto late with the winner guaranteed a place in
the quarterinals. Australia would get the other place if it beats
the United States in Tuesday's late game and still might advance
even if it loses.
	   On Monday, Yugoslavia fell to Italy 61-60 _ probably the key
upset of the tournament _ as the Italians avenged a loss last year
in the final of the European championship to the Yugoslavs.
	   And they were undone by two of their own from the former
Yugoslavia _ Bosnian-born Bodjan Tanjevic, the Italian coach, and
Slovenian-born Gregor Fucka, who hit the winning shots.
	   The Americans improved to 4-1 with 17 from Jimmy Oliver and 12
from Brad Miller in a 75-73 win over Spain.
	   Russia demolished the host Greeks 60-48 as Sergei Babkov hit 18,
one of four in double figures. Greece was led by Fragiskos Albertis
with 12 points.
	   Lithuania, bronze medalists in the last two Olympics, beat
Argentina 84-75. Australia improved its chances of reaching the
quarterfinals with a 75-63 come-from-behind victory over Brazil.
	   Puerto Rico also stayed alive for a quarterfinal berth with a
94-81 victory over Canada.
	   (scw) 	   
</TEXT>
