<HEADLINE>
Golarsa beats No. 2 seed in first round
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ISTANBUL, Turkey (AP) _ Italy's Laura Golarsa ousted tournament
No. 2 seed Sabine Appelmans Tuesday in the first round of the dlrs
107,500 Enka Open tournament.
	   Golarsa, ranked 86th on the WTA list, beat Appelmans, of
Belgium, 7-6 (12-10), 6-3.
	   Meghann Shaughnessy, of the U.S., scored an upset 6-3, 6-4 win
over No. 5 seed Tatiana Panova, of Russia.
	   While, Belarus' Olga Barabanschikova defeated French player Alex
Dechaume-Balleret 6-0, 6-3.
