reporting fires far from the actual blazes.
	   ``There was an attempt to terrorize firefighting forces and
cause anxiety,'' said Public Order Minister Giorgos Romeos.
	   No injuries due to the fires were reported. Blazes in the
Pendeli area in past years have left much of the mountainside a
landscape of charred stumps.
	   A separate large fire broke out near the southeastern seaside
resort suburb of Lagonisi. No houses or hotels were threatened, and
it also had died down by evening.
	   In another brush fire, flames had threatened some ancient sites
including the small amphitheater at Epidavros, about 60 kilometers
(35 miles) southwest of Athens, media reports said.
	   Two weeks ago, three firefighters and a volunteer firefighter
were killed battling a blaze that scorched the eastern edge of
Athens.
	   Wildfires are common during the hot and dry summers in Greece.
But this season has been called one of the most devastating in
decades, with fires burning daily for the past month.
</TEXT>
