<HEADLINE>
Hardline Kosovo Albanian group slams European powers
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TIRANA, Albania (AP) _ A hard-line group of Kosovo Albanians
condemned European powers Tuesday for failing to react to the
latest Serb offensive in the Serbian province of Kosovo, Albanian
media reported.
	   The Popular Movement of Kosovo, a group supporting the
underground Kosovo Liberation Army, said in a statement issued to
state-run Albanian TV that ``with their silence, European
politicians are helping Serbia to use violence against Kosovo,''
where the rebel KLA is fighting Serb forces for independence.
	   ``The last Serbian offensive against the people of Kosovo and
KLA was aimed at eliminating the Kosovo Liberation Army forces ...
and forcing Kosovo Albanians to give up their fight for liberty and
democracy, and finally to have a government in Kosovo that is
sympathetic to Belgrade.''
	   By not acting against the Serbs, said the Switzerland-based
movement, European leaders are supporting ``the Serbian regime and
(Yugoslav President Slobodan) Milosevic.''
	   The statement also said ``assured the international community''
that the KLA would not be brought down to its knees.
	   (me/rp)
