<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Jane's-India Guns </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Jane's: India negotiating spares for controversial guns
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ India is finalizing the purchase of much needed
spare parts for 410 howitzers bought from the Swedish weapons
company Bofors AB in a deal that continues to rock Indian politics,
Jane's Defense Weekly reported Tuesday.
	   Official sources in India were quoted by the respected military
magazine as saying that military and Ministry of Defense officials
were completing negotiations with two Bofors subsidiaries,
CelsiusTech in Sweden and AB Celsius in Austria, for spares for the
155 mm towed howitzers.
	   For nearly 10 years, Jane's said, all dealings with Bofors and
its subsidiaries have been banned because of a corruption scandal.
	   The Indian government enacted an embargo against Bofors after it
was revealed that the Swedish company allegedly paid kickbacks of
dlrs 50 million to secure the 1986 howitzer deal with India. The
scandal brought down the government of Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi,
and investigations are still continuing.
	   Since the early 1990s, Jane's said, the howitzers have
increasingly been suffering from a shortage of spare parts which
has led to widespread cannibalization. The howitzers have undergone
over 130 modifications and between 100 and 120 are inoperative, it
said.
	   Earlier attempts by the army to persuade successive Indian
governments to import spares for the howitzers failed, the magazine
said.
	   ``However, the situation has now become so acute that the only
options are either to buy a new weapon system for which there is no
money or to buy the spares from a Bofor subsidiary,'' it said.
	   Jane's also reported that Indian defense officials have visited
Britain and Israel to buy specialized equipment for the country's
special forces including submachine guns, sniper rifles, night
vision devices and crossbows. The equipment is mainly for use
against Kashmiri militants fighting for an Islamic homeland, it
said.
	   (eml-rs) 	   
</TEXT>
