<HEADLINE>
Mexico's ICA gets $11 million IFC loan for cruise ship terminal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MEXICO CITY (AP) _ Empresas ICA SA, a leading Mexican
construction company, said Tuesday it received a dlrs 11 million
loan to build a Caribbean cruise line terminal.
	   The Punta Langosta Cruise Line Terminal in the Mexican port city
of Cozumel is expected to generate more than dlrs 4 million in
annual billings, ICA said in a news release. ICA plans to begin
operations in November. The dock will be able to receive cruise
ships of more than 70,000 tons.
	   ICA said the loan from the International Finance Corp. is to be
repaid in two installments: dlrs 7 million within 10 years and dlrs
4 million within 12 years. The project's total cost is estimated at
dlrs 19.6 million.
