<SLUG> BC-Congo-Who's Who, 1st Ld-Writethru,0299 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A list of key figures and groups in Congo
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS Rwandan Tutsis &QL; 
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   _President Laurent Kabila: former Marxist and rebel leader who
swept to power last year after his forces toppled longtime dictator
Mobutu Sese Seko. A member of the Luba tribe from Congo's Katanga
province, he relied heavily on armed support from Rwandan Tutsi
soldiers and Banyamulenge Tutsis for support during his rebel war
in 1997.
	   _Banyamulenge ethnic group: Congolese Tutsis based predominantly
in the country's east. Share close ties with Rwandan Tutsis and
played an important military role in Kabila's rebel victory over
Mobutu. Along with Rwandan troops, the Banyamulenge are the lead
players in the current uprising in Congo.
	   _Col. James Kabarere: A Rwandan Tutsi soldier who was recently
fired as Kabila's chief military commander. Known while working for
Kabila as James Kabari. Wields significant influence among Rwandan
troops who fought alongside Kabila and now are staging a rebellion
against his government. Was reportedly in eastern town of Bukavu
during uprising.
	   _Rwandan Tutsis: Ethnic group leading Rwanda's government.
Kabila last week ordered all Rwandan soldiers out of the country,
setting the stage for the latest rebellion.
	   _Rwandan Vice President and Defense Minister Paul Kagame: born
in exile in Uganda. Joined rebel forces of current Ugandan
President Yoweri Museveni, then left to join the rebel Rwandan
Patriotic Front. After the death of its founder, Kagame assumed
control and after the 1994 genocide, led rebel forces who overthrew
Rwanda's extremist Hutu government. Kagame is widely believed to be
responsible for masterminding the rebellion that put Kabila in
power in Congo.
</TEXT>
