<HEADLINE>
With Israel-Romania
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Israel and Romania to establish forum on return of Jewish property
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with Israeli legislator describing meeting as tense,
report Vasile angered in graf 3 &QL; 
 &UR; By DINA KRAFT &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Israel and Romania agreed Tuesday to establish
a joint parliamentary forum to resolve a dispute over the return of
Jewish property seized after World War II, Israeli lawmakers said.
	   The decision was taken by visiting Romanian Prime Minister Radu
Vasile and Israeli lawmakers who agreed to a forum for dialogue
between their respective parliaments until a solution can be found,
Israeli legislator Avraham Poraz said.
	   Poraz described the meeting with Vasile as ``heated,'' and
Israel Radio reported after a state dinner Tuesday night that
Vasile was angered by the way he was pressured at the meeting.
