<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Spain-Immigrant </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Moroccan facing police questioning jumps out of courthouse window
</HEADLINE>
in Spain

<TEXT>
	   ALGECIRAS, Spain (AP) _ A young Moroccan awaiting questioning
over drugs found in a small, crowded boat in which he tried to
sneak into Spain jumped out of a courthouse window on Tuesday,
suffering serious injuries.
	   The Civil Guard in this southern port said the man fell 10
meters (33 feet) and landed on a staircase. He was rushed to
hospital in serious condition. A spokesman refused to detail the
injuries or give the man's name or age.
	   He was picked up Monday in a small boat that crossed the Strait
of Gibraltar from Morocco with 30 men aboard. Police found 10 kilos
(22 pounds) of hashish in it.
	   In another boat police picked up 25 men and two women, all of
them would-be immigrants. Both boats were intercepted just off the
southern coast of Spain.
	   Fleeing poverty at home, thousands of people attempt each year
to cross the Mediterranean Sea from North Africa and slip into
Europe. Almost all of them are men, and most are from Morocco.
	   Some 20 would-be immigrants are believed to have drowned when
their boat overturned close to the Spanish coast last week.
	   Those caught in Spain or trying to make the crossing are
repatriated.
	   dw
</TEXT>
