<SLUG> BC-Mexico-Citibank,0125 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Citibank pays dlrs 195 million for Confia purchase in Mexico
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MEXICO CITY (AP) _ Citibank has paid about dlrs 195 million to
Mexico's bank savings protection fund for a local bank, Confia SA,
a Citibank official said Tuesday.
	   Madeleine Girot, a spokeswoman for Citibank Mexico, said the
payment was made on Friday to the fund known as Fobaproa.
	   The government awarded Citibank rights to purchase Confia in
August 1997 after federal regulators stepped in when the bank's
previous owners were unable to meet capital requirements.
	   Confia's network of 200 branches is expected to be merged into
Citibank in the next three to five years. The U.S. bank assumed
management control of Confia in mid-May.
</TEXT>
