<SLUG> BC-Israel-Shooting, 2nd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Two Jewish settlers shot and killed outside West Bank settlement
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES throughout with background on Israeli-Palestinians
talks, settler lobby opposed to withdrawal &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   TEL AVIV, Israel (AP) _ Two Jewish settlers were shot and killed
while patrolling their West Bank settlement of Itzhar early
Wednesday, The Israeli army said.
	   Israel placed a curfew on four surrounding Palestinian villages
and said it was searching the area for the shooters.
	   The killings come at a tense time in Israeli-Palestinian peace
talks where the two sides have been unable to agree on the scope of
a long overdue Israeli troop withdrawal from West Bank territory.
	   ``Two citizens were killed tonight at the Itzhar settlement near
Nablus from shots fired at their patrol jeep,'' the army statement
said.
	   Settler spokesman Ahron Dombe said the shooting occurred at
approximately 1:00am (22:00gmt).
	   Itzhar is located 10km (6 miles) south of the Palestinian-run
city of Nablus, West Bank.
	   Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has been under immense
pressure from the strong Jewish settler lobby and right-wing
members of his Cabinet to reject an American peace initiative which
calls for Israel to withdraw troops from an additional 13 percent
of the West Bank.
	   Tuesday, the Palestinians rejected an Israeli proposal to
pullback its forces from ten percent and turn an additional 3
percent into a nature reserve.
	   The two sides have spent a little over two weeks in direct talks
which have not led to any breakthrough and the Palestinians have
said they were considering walking away from the negotiations.
 &UR; dl
</TEXT>
