<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Liverpool-Inter </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ince shines as Liverpool wins 2-1
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LIVERPOOL, England (AP) _ Paul Ince outshone teen-age star
Michael Owen as Liverpool edged his former club Inter Milan 2-1
Tuesday in a pre-season warmup game at Anfield.
	   Ince, who joined Liverpool from Inter last season, fired his
team ahead in the 31st minute when his first shot from 25 meters
(yards) was blocked by 'keeper Gianluca Pagliuca and the midfielder
followed up to shoot home.
	   Inter, who agreed to the game as part of the transfer deal
involving Ince, leveled through Cristiano Zanetti, but Liverpool
substitute Steve Harkness fired the winner with 14 minutes left.
	   Much of the pre-match talk was about 18-year-old Owen, who
scored a stunning World Cup goal for England and looks a huge
prospect. Although he impressed with his runs, he was closely
marked by Francesco Colonnese.
	   (rjm)	   
</TEXT>
