<SLUG> BC-Brazil-Telephone Privatization,0140 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Telephone companies formalize privatization in Brazil
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) _ The telecommunications companies who
bought parts of state-run phone company Telebras formalized the
deal with the government Tuesday.
	   Telebras was split into 12 separate companies that were
auctioned off for a total of 22 billion reals (dlrs 19 billion)
last Wednesday in Latin America's biggest privatization to date.
	   MCI bought Embratel, and Spain's Telefonica and Portugal Telecom
came away with the lion's share of the fixed line and celluar
services.
	   Officials from the Rio de Janeiro Stock Exchange, where the
auction was held, handed Communications Minister Luiz Carlos
Mendonca de Barros a check for 8.82 billion reals (dlrs 7.6
billion), 40 per cent purchase price as a down payment.
</TEXT>
