<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-RugbyU-New Zealand Team </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Three veterans dropped from New Zealand side
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AUCKLAND, New Zealand (AP) _ Veteran New Zealand flanker Michael
Jones, his longtime partner Mark Carter and Walter Little have paid
the price for the All Blacks' three consecutive rugby union losses
in the Tri Nations series.
	   All three were dropped from the team that will leave for South
Africa on Friday for its last Tri Nations match on Aug. 15 in
Durban.
	   Norm Berryman has been included in the All Blacks for the first
time while Auckland fullback Adrian Cashmore has been recalled for
the first time since his axing ahead of the tour to Britain last
year.
	   Flanker Josh Kronfeld will require a clearance Thursday from a
concussion he suffered in the match against South Africa in
Wellington before he can join the 26-man squad.
	   Not considered because of injury were prop Mark Allen (back),
hooker Norm Hewitt (knee), Alama Ieremia (foot) and center Caleb
Ralph (thigh).
	   Hart said the omission of the 55-test veteran Jones resulted
from a need to look ahead to next year.
	   ``I know Michael would love to have gone to South Africa but he
understands we are now looking at players to take us through to the
rugby World Cup,'' Hart said.
	   Jones said in a statement he realized the focus of the team was
next year.
	   ``I was dearly looking forward to contributing to an All Black
team going to South Africa and Australia to restore some pride and
to have the opportunity to be in a winning All Black team again.
However, I understand why the selectors are bringing on some new
players.
	   ``They have made it clear it is nothing to do with my form and I
respect their decision to look ahead to next year.''
	   Little is being rested partly owing to form and an ongoing foot
injury.
	   The New Zealand team: Christian Cullen, Adrian Cashmore, Jeff
Wilson, Jonah Lomu, Joeli Vidiri, Norman Berryman, Scott McLeod,
Mark Mayerhofler, Carlos Spencer, Andrew Mehrtens, Mark Robinson,
Justin Marshall, Ofisa Tonu'u, Isitolo Maka, Taine Randell
(captain), Josh Kronfeld, Scott Robertson, Charles Riechelmann,
Royce Willis, Robin Brooke, Ian Jones, Olo Brown, Craig Dowd, Carl
Hoeft, Anton Oliver, Mark Hammett. (djp) 	   
</TEXT>
