<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-US Open Cup,0103 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Crew 1, MetroStars 0
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEW ORLEANS (AP) _ Ricardo Iribarren scored in the fifth minute
Tuesday night, and the Columbus Crew beat the New York-New Jersey
MetroStars 1-0 to advance to the final of the U.S. Open Cup.
	   Columbus, third in Major League Soccer's Eastern Conference,
will play either Chicago or Dallas for the championship. The Fire
and the Burn played in the second game of the doubleheader.
	   Iribarren beat goalkeeper Tony Meola off a cross from Andrew
Williams.
	   The MetroStars are second in the Eastern Conference, trailing
D.C. United.
</TEXT>
